Here's how to set up a Django project, install Django REST Framework, and create the messaging app:

Step 1: Initialize a new Django project
First, navigate to the directory where you want to create your project in your terminal or command prompt. Then, run the following command:

django-admin startproject messaging_app

This will create a new directory named messaging_app with the basic Django project structure.

Step 2: Install Django REST Framework
Navigate into your newly created project directory:

cd messaging_app

Now, create a virtual environment (recommended for dependency management):

python -m venv venv

Activate the virtual environment:

On Windows:

.\venv\Scripts\activate

On macOS/Linux:

source venv/bin/activate

Once the virtual environment is active, install Django and Django REST Framework:

pip install Django djangorestframework

Step 3: Set up Django REST Framework in settings.py
Open the messaging_app/settings.py file in your project. Find the INSTALLED_APPS list and add 'rest_framework' to it.

Your INSTALLED_APPS section should look something like this:

# messaging_app/settings.py

INSTALLED_APPS = [
    'django.contrib.admin',
    'django.contrib.auth',
    'django.contrib.contenttypes',
    'django.contrib.sessions',
    'django.contrib.messages',
    'django.contrib.staticfiles',
    'rest_framework',  # Add this line
    # Your other apps will go here
]

# You can also add REST_FRAMEWORK settings for global configuration (optional for now)
# REST_FRAMEWORK = {
#     'DEFAULT_PERMISSION_CLASSES': [
#         'rest_framework.permissions.AllowAny',
#     ]
# }

Step 4: Create a new app for messaging functionality
While still in the messaging_app directory (where manage.py is located), run the following command to create your chats app:

python manage.py startapp chats

Finally, add your new chats app to the INSTALLED_APPS list in messaging_app/settings.py as well:

# messaging_app/settings.py

INSTALLED_APPS = [
    'django.contrib.admin',
    'django.contrib.auth',
    'django.contrib.contenttypes',
    'django.contrib.sessions',
    'django.contrib.messages',
    'django.contrib.staticfiles',
    'rest_framework',
    'chats',  # Add this line
]

You have now successfully set up your Django project with Django REST Framework and created your chats app!
